begin_memory_text: We spoke about her schooling, she said that she was in school for child psychology and she worked a job. I spoke about being in school in the past and how stressful having a job could be while being in school.
middle_memory_text: We spoke about family, she said she had a younger brother and I spoke about my siblings and I went on a tangent about moving and being in a car accident. She spoke about being a researcher for her job.
end_memory_text: I mainly spoke toward the end about my mishaps in life and she gave positive feedback about not giving up, we also spoke about her journey in school and we wished each other good luck in our endeavors.
rest_of_day_open: I plan to take down my hair, which is a two-day process of washing, moisturizing, setting, and styling. I also plan to write my story and work on building a website for myself. I will be learning through the Adobe workshop how to build book covers and helping with the business, by creating labels and selling products. I imagine that I will sleep well, and get in exercise and stay away from bad foods.
critical_positive: I liked that she was a college student who was dedicated to paying down her debts, working her way through the system with a clear plan ahead. She was friendly and warm and accepting of my rambles and did not appear to be judgemental. I found my chat partner pleasant to speak with.
critical_negative: I tend to disrupt to flow of conversation and often self-disclose to make conversation. It is something I am working on, but going on tangents is disruptive in a way that the other person do not get a chance to speak as much. I need to listen more and talk less.

begin_memory_text: We talked about a lot of things. I think my partner kept asking me a bunch of unrelated questions. So I remember talking about school, both being interested in psychology. She mentioned having some broken bones but I didn't want to inquire and be rude.
middle_memory_text: I think once we warmed up a bit and I got a better sense of her personality things started going a lot smoother. We talked about where we lived (she's in the midwest and I'm on the east coast). She asked if it was snowing here which surprised me, but said there was a blizzard there. We talked a bit about how she worked at an airline and the hierarchy and competitive nature there.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation, the connection on her end seemed to go in and out. Her video was a bit blurry but I could still hear & see her fine. I also got the sense my video was lagging on her end which is why there were times it seemed like interrupting or awkward. We talked more about her moving from Minnesot to Arizona to Florida and back. We talked a bit more about her accident which I felt kind bad for asking follow up questions but she kept brining it up in conversation, so I got the sense she wanted to talk about it. I was trying my best to be respectful though.
rest_of_day_open: Last week was really rough for me and over the weekend I had a bit of a mental breakdown. I'm really trying for this week to be on the upswing and get my act together. I'm hoping that my workload will be a bit manageable. My schedule doesn't change too often, but I am seeing friends (socially distanced) this weekend so that will be a nice time.
critical_positive: I think she was really talkative and put herself out there. At the end she said she was shy and tends to ramble when talking to strangers, but I thought the conversation was okay. She was also really friendly and seemed to be very open minded. I consider her a nice person and wouldn't mind talking to her again, but Im not sure if I could see us being more than friendly acquaintances.
critical_negative: At first, she might have been nervous, she kept asking a bunch of questions that didn't really go together. I remember looking at the time and only 10 minutes had passed and I thought "oh no this will drag and be awkward" but then the conversation got better. I think we spent more time talking about her but I was okay with just listening for the most part. She did try to reciprocate at times, but kept bringing up her disability which made me feel a bit uncomfortable since I wasn't sure what to say and felt anything I could say to try and relate would be considered trivial.
